description:
You are an HVAC maintenance supervisor. Research the EPA's AIM Act refrigerant phasedown regulations and create a compliance guide for your team. Your research must include the AIM Act phasedown schedule (percentage reductions for 2024, 2029, and 2036), at least three approved alternative refrigerants to replace R-410A (including their GWP and ASHRAE safety classification), and whether Section 608 certification, venting, and recordkeeping requirements apply to these new refrigerants. Create a Firefox bookmark folder named 'HVAC Regulatory Research' containing at least four relevant bookmarks from EPA.gov and industry sources. Compile all findings into a JSON file at '~/Documents/refrigerant_compliance_guide.json' using the following structure:

{
  "aim_act": {
    "signed_into_law": "YYYY",
    "phasedown_2024_pct": <number>,
    "phasedown_2029_pct": <number>,
    "phasedown_2036_pct": <number>
  },
  "refrigerants": {
    "R-410A": { "gwp": <number>, "ashrae_safety_class": "A1" },
    "<Alternative_1>": { "gwp": <number>, "ashrae_safety_class": "..." },
    "<Alternative_2>": { "gwp": <number>, "ashrae_safety_class": "..." },
    "<Alternative_3>": { "gwp": <number>, "ashrae_safety_class": "..." }
  },
  "section_608": {
    "certification_required": <boolean>,
    "venting_prohibited": <boolean>,
    "recordkeeping_required": <boolean>
  }
}
